UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Teddy Leonel CRUZ-VELEZ, a.k.a. Rene Ortega, a.k.a. Juan Dunn, a.k.a. Jet Ski, a.k.a. Rene Negron-Ortiz, a.k.a. Benjamin Marrero, a.k.a. Renee Ortiz-Negron, a.k.a. Hector Nieve, a.k.a. Jose Dubal, Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-12951

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Sept. 29, 2010. Before EDMONDSON, MARTIN and KRAVITCH, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Richard A. Selinger, appointed counsel for Teddy Leonel Cruz-Velez in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Cruz-Velez’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
